               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0091AQM">ʾAgarhǝse ʾAbuna Māmās</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1689" notAfter="1693">On <locus target="#26ra">26ra</locus>, and elsewhere, ʾIyasu is mentioned as the reigning king.
                        On <locus target="#28vb">28vb</locus>, etc., Yoḥannǝs is mentioned as the
                        patriarch and Sinodā as the metropolitan; and on <locus target="#28va">28va</locus>, Marqos is mentioned as the metropolitan. ʾIyasu I was the
                        king of Ethiopia in 1682-1706, John XVI was Patriarch of Alexandria in
                        1676-1718, Sinodā was metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1671-93, Marqos IV was
                        metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1689-1716 (for four years Sinodā and Marqos held
                        the office of the Metropolitan jointly due to the ecclesiastical policies of
                        ʾIyasu I).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Supplication formulas mention ʾabuna Mikāʾel; sometimes he is mentioned together
                     with his brother Misaʾel (s. 43ra, 53vb, 93rb,
                     etc.).</provenance></history>
